{
  "texts": [
    "In all cases the time evolution is characterised by a product of hypergeometric functions.",
    "Notations and conventions.Throughout this paper, we adopt natural units c = ℏ = 1 and work with the (-+ ++) metric sign convention.",
    "Fourier transforms are defined byf (x) = d 3 k (2π) 3 e ik•x f (k) ≡ k e ik•x f (k).",
    "(1.3)We will always adhere to exact translational and rotational invariance.",
    "In fact, we shall work in the Poincaré patch of de Sitter space with the metric as an approximation for an inflationary spacetime."
  ]
}